</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,617,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The generic epithet is a combination of the generic names 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1839" box="[897,1029,617,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Sclerosomatidae" genus="Leiobunum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[897,1029,617,643]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Leiobunum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1091,1182,617,643]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1910" box="[1091,1179,617,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Gagrellidae" genus="Nelima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nelima</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
